Figure 1: Interactive P5.js Boids simulation showing emergent flocking behavior










Note



About this simulation: This interactive visualization demonstrates Craig Reynolds’ “boids” algorithm, which simulates flocking behavior through simple rules: separation (avoid crowding neighbors), alignment (steer towards average heading of neighbors), and cohesion (steer towards average position of neighbors). The emergent complexity from these simple rules exemplifies key concepts in generative media.



